      <PrimaryExemptPurposeTxt>THE PRIMARY PURPOSE OF THE CORPORATION IS TO PROMOTE AND FOSTER ASSISTANCE AND SUPPORT TO DISTRESSED, UNDERPRIVILEGED AND IMPOVERISHED INDIVIDUALS AND/OR COMMUNITIES THROUGHOUT THE WORLD; WHICH MAY BE ACCOMPLISHED IN PART BY WORKING TO CONNECT MARGINALIZED AND VICTIMIZED PEOPLE WITH RESOURCES FROM FAITH BASED GROUPS, GOVERNMENT GROUPS, COMMUNITY ORGANIZATIONS, AND INDIVIDUALS TO IMPROVE QUALITY OF LIFE AND BRING ABOUT OPPORTUNITIES FOR LIFE TRANSFORMATION AND PERSONAL DEVELOPMENT AND OPERATE IN A MANNER CONSISTENT WITH ORGANIZATIONS THAT ARE EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXATION UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE OF 10986.</PrimaryExemptPurposeTxt>
      <ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
        <DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>CCSHH (CENTRO CRISTIANO DE SERVICIOS HUMANITARIOS DE HONDURAS) IS AN EYE AND DENTAL CLINIC ESTABLISHED IN 1997 FOR THE PURPOSE OF SERVING THE UNDERSERVED POPULATION IN THE YORO AREA, ALTHOUGH IT WELCOMES ALL PATIENTS WHO QUALIFY. OVER 20,000 PATIENTS ARE SEEN AT THE CLINIC EACH YEAR AND OVER 1,500 EYE SURGERIES PERFORMED. THE PATIENTS WHO RECEIVE CARE AT CCSHH ARE THOSE WHO CANNOT AFFORD MEDICAL AND DENTAL CARE IN THE PRIVATE SECTOR.</DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>
        <GrantsAndAllocationsAmt>86100</GrantsAndAllocationsAmt>
        <ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>7337</ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>
      </ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
      <ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
        <DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>GSF (GOOD SAMARITAN FUND) IS A PROGRAM STARTED IN 1998 IN EL PROGRESO, YORO, AS AN HUMANITARIAN EFFORT TO ADDRESS SOME OF THE MANY NEEDS OF THE UNDERSERVED PEOPLE IN THIS AREA. THE GSF SUPPLIES BASIC NECESSITIES OF EVERYDAY LIFE FOR CHILDREN AND FAMILIES WHO QUALIFY. SOME OF THE ASSISTANCE COMES IN THE FORM OF BAGS OF BASIC FOOD SUPPLIES EACH MONTH. SCHOOL SUPPLIES AND UNIFORMS ARE SUPPLIED TO CHILDREN AND YOUTH WHO QUALIFY FOR OUR ASSISTANCE PROGRAM. GSF ALSO AIDS THE COMMUNITY DURING TIMES OF NATURAL DISASTERS, SUCH AS HURRICANES AND FLOODING. IT SERVES AS A CRISIS INTERVENTION PROGRAM. HOT MEALS ARE PREPARED AND DISTRIBUTED TO HUNDREDS OF PEOPLE WHO HAVE LOST THEIR HOMES DUE TO FLOODING. PERSONAL HYGIENE KITS ARE GIVEN TO THOSE IN NEED.</DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>
        <GrantsAndAllocationsAmt>17711</GrantsAndAllocationsAmt>
        <ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>27538</ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>
      </ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
      <ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
        <DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>THE ENDOWMENT FUND WAS ESTABLISHED IN 2016. THESE FUNDS ARE SET ASIDE FOR ANY MAJOR NEEDS THE CLINIC MIGHT HAVE. CURRENTLY THE CLINIC IS PLANNING AN EXPANSION OF ITS PHYSICAL PLANT AND SOME OF THE ENDOWMENT FUND WILL BE USED FOR THE COST OF THIS EXPANSION. THE FUND WAS ALSO ESTABLISHED TO GUARANTEE THE CLINIC AND VISION'S OTHER PROGRAMS WILL CONTINUE IN THE FUTURE.</DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>
